de.bioforscher.singa.chemistry.physical.leaves

Class AminoAcid

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.bioforscher.singa.chemistry.physical.leaves.LeafSubstructure<AminoAcid,AminoAcidFamily>
      • de.bioforscher.singa.chemistry.physical.leaves.AminoAcid
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Exchangeable<AminoAcidFamily>, StructuralEntity<AminoAcid,LeafIdentifier>, Substructure<AminoAcid,LeafIdentifier>, Nameable, Graph<Atom,Bond,java.lang.Integer>, Node<AminoAcid,Vector3D,LeafIdentifier>

    public class AminoAcid
extends LeafSubstructure<AminoAcid,AminoAcidFamily>
    A AminoAcid is a grouping element that should only contain atoms. Each and every AminoAcid has a associate ResidueType, that determines the amino acid (and the overarching features).

      • AminoAcid

        public AminoAcid(AminoAcid aminoAcid)
        This is a copy constructor. Creates a new amino acid with the same attributes as the given amino acid. This also recursively creates copies of all the underlying substructures and atoms. The neighbours of this substructure are NOT copied. Due to the nature of this operation it would be bad to keep a part of the relations to the lifecycle of the substructure to copy. If you want to keep the neighbouring substructures, copy the superordinate substructure that contains this substructure and it will also traverse and copy the neighbouring substructures.
        Parameters:
        aminoAcid - The amino acid to copy
